The paper deals with algorithms for graph optimization problems, specifically the densest subgraph problem, in the streaming and RAM models. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the categories of Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS), Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM), and Computational Complexity (cs.CC). The paper also discusses the use of sampling techniques, which could place it in the category of Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) or Machine Learning (cs.LG).
